{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "a834cf420d671142", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#choose-your-api-provider", "position": 4, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["provider", "choose this when"], "cells": ["Microsoft Foundry", "You want to inherit existing Azure compliance controls and billing"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#choose-your-api-provider", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md", "anchor": "choose-your-api-provider", "breadcrumb": "Set up Claude Code for your organization > Choose your API provider", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "Claude Code connects to Claude through one of several API providers. Your choice affects billing, authentication, and which compliance posture you inherit.\n\nFor the full provider comparison covering authentication, regions, and feature parity, see the enterprise deployment overview. Each provider's auth setup is in Authentication.\n\nProxy and firewall requirements in Network configuration apply regardless of provider. If you want a single endpoint in front of multiple providers or centralized request logging, see LLM gateway.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["http://claude.ai"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "d537ba7c7ffe718d", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-how-settings-reach-devices", "position": 0, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["mechanism", "delivery", "priority", "platforms"], "cells": ["Server-managed", "Claude.ai admin console", "Highest", "All"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "2b046e9dd4049202", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-how-settings-reach-devices", "position": 1, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["mechanism", "delivery", "priority", "platforms"], "cells": ["plist / registry policy", "macOS: `com.anthropic.claudecode` plistWindows: `HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\ClaudeCode`", "High", "macOS, Windows"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "42afe2924227352f", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-how-settings-reach-devices", "position": 2, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["mechanism", "delivery", "priority", "platforms"], "cells": ["File-based managed", "macOS: `/Library/Application Support/ClaudeCode/managed-settings.json`Linux and WSL: `/etc/claude-code/managed-settings.json`Windows: `C:\\Program Files\\ClaudeCode\\managed-settings.json`", "Medium", "All"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "d96e803ce54dcb4e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-how-settings-reach-devices", "position": 3, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["mechanism", "delivery", "priority", "platforms"], "cells": ["Windows user registry", "`HKCU\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\ClaudeCode`", "Lowest", "Windows only"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-how-settings-reach-devices", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md", "anchor": "decide-how-settings-reach-devices", "breadcrumb": "Set up Claude Code for your organization > Decide how settings reach devices", "level": 2, "position": 2, "text": "Managed settings define policy that takes precedence over local developer configuration. Claude Code looks for them in four places and uses the first one it finds on a given device.\n\nServer-managed settings reach devices at authentication time and refresh hourly during active sessions, with no endpoint infrastructure. They require a Claude for Teams or Enterprise plan, so deployments on other providers need one of the file-based or OS-level mechanisms instead.\n\nIf your organization mixes providers, configure server-managed settings for Claude.ai users plus a file-based or plist/registry fallback so other users still receive managed policy.\n\nThe plist and HKLM registry locations work with any provider and resist tampering because they require admin privileges to write. The Windows user registry at HKCU is writable without elevation, so treat it as a convenience default rather than an enforcement channel.\n\nBy default WSL reads only the Linux file path at `/etc/claude-code`. To extend your Windows registry and `C:\\Program Files\\ClaudeCode` policy to WSL on the same machine, set `wslInheritsWindowsSettings: true` in either of those admin-only Windows sources.\n\nWhichever mechanism you choose, managed values take precedence over user and project settings. Array settings such as `permissions.allow` and `permissions.deny` merge entries from all sources, so developers can extend managed lists but not remove from them.\n\nSee Server-managed settings and Settings files and precedence.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["http://Claude.ai"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "5532492ada561eb5", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 0, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Permission rules", "Allow, ask, or deny specific tools and commands", "`permissions.allow`, `permissions.deny`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "ee4c6e9ce68f2848", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 1, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Permission lockdown", "Only managed permission rules apply; disable `--dangerously-skip-permissions`", "`allowManagedPermissionRulesOnly`, `permissions.disableBypassPermissionsMode`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "a11f77a61d61fad8", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 2, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Sandboxing", "OS-level filesystem and network isolation with domain allowlists", "`sandbox.enabled`, `sandbox.network.allowedDomains`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "27ae4001c2538e91", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 3, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Managed policy CLAUDE.md", "Org-wide instructions loaded in every session, cannot be excluded", "File at the managed policy path"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "adbe31ac323c0833", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 4, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["MCP server control", "Restrict which MCP servers users can add or connect to", "`allowedMcpServers`, `deniedMcpServers`, `allowManagedMcpServersOnly`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "599eb15f49396de9", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 5, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Plugin marketplace control", "Restrict which marketplace sources users can add and install from", "`strictKnownMarketplaces`, `blockedMarketplaces`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "d384ab9d2bad85ad", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 6, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Hook restrictions", "Only managed hooks load; restrict HTTP hook URLs", "`allowManagedHooksOnly`, `allowedHttpHookUrls`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "70f4eef78af2afc9", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "position": 7, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["control", "what it does", "key settings"], "cells": ["Version floor", "Prevent auto-update from installing below an org-wide minimum", "`minimumVersion`"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md#decide-what-to-enforce", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/admin-setup.md", "anchor": "decide-what-to-enforce", "breadcrumb": "Set up Claude Code for your organization > Decide what to enforce", "level": 2, "position": 3, "text": "Managed settings can lock down tools, sandbox execution, restrict MCP servers and plugin sources, and control which hooks run. Each row is a control surface with the setting keys that drive it.\n\nPermission rules and sandboxing cover different layers. Denying WebFetch blocks Claude's fetch tool, but if Bash is allowed, `curl` and `wget` can still reach any URL. Sandboxing closes that gap with a network domain allowlist enforced at the OS level.\n\nFor the threat model these controls defend against, see Security.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
